            <div id="dsq-comment-message-43230" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>We did shutter some non-performing businesses during the 2009 downturn. We did not lay off 14% of the staff. And we were not forced to, as we were in 2001. We were using the opportunity to increase our focus on what was working.</p>
</div>
