            <div id="dsq-comment-message-43207" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>This was a real eye-opener Tim, thank you! I am as euphoric and idealistic the same way you was (and hopefully still are, even if you lost hair) regarding the HR policies you published some years ago. It is the real way to go combined with a healthy way of implementing the principle &#8220;Happiness is positive cash flow.&#8221; (this statement is packed with wisdom). People can love their work and be aware of their financial responsibilities at the same time. It is the moment when people really realize who else depends on their work. Not only the company, but colleagues and their families (of course their own families as well). Children are the creative minds of tomorrow and the next tax payers in line. Regarding venture capital and investors I strongly agree with @JoeBuck:disqus .</p>
