        <div id="dsq-comment-body-43228" class="dsq-comment-body">
            <div id="dsq-comment-message-43228" class="dsq-comment-message"><p>Not enough leaders take time to reflect on the past and try to improve for the future. I guess that&#8217;s one of the reasons I enjoy reading Tim O&#8217;Reilly&#8217;s writings. </p>
<p>Take a look at Microsoft. It&#8217;s become a debacle of a company, squandering their industry leads on successful products, missing great opportunities for new products, etc. I hear far more stories about what a terrible environment it is to work in, than anything else. The leadership takes no time to reflect on what about their company helps them succeed, and what is leading them towards failure. As a result, they simply are barreling ahead on auto-pilot.</p>
